/// Learnable Residual Connection
///
/// A residual connection with learnable scaling factors (alpha, beta).
/// Instead of the standard `x + sublayer(x)`, computes:
///   output = alpha * skip + beta * main
/// where alpha and beta are learnable scalar parameters per-layer.
///
/// This gives the model fine-grained control over how much each
/// sublayer contributes to the residual stream. Inspired by
/// DeepSeek-V3's training stability innovations.
///
/// Parameters:
/// - dim: Feature dimension (for initialization, not used in forward)
///
/// Shape Contract:
/// - Input main: [*shape, dim] — sublayer output
/// - Input skip: [*shape, dim] — residual/skip connection
/// - Output: [*shape, dim] — weighted combination
///
/// Notes:
/// - alpha initialized to 1.0, beta initialized to 1.0 (starts as standard residual)
/// - During training, the model learns to adjust these per-layer
/// - Helps with gradient flow in very deep networks (40+ layers)
///
/// Reference: DeepSeek-V3 Technical Report (2024)
neuron LearnableResidual(dim):
    in main: [*shape, dim]
    in skip: [*shape, dim]
    out: [*shape, dim]
    impl: neuroscript,connections/LearnableResidual
